/// A pure `func → Eff`: `zip` the mmap (its base is an inert `rawptr`) with the file size, then `|> mem.bound`
/// folds (address, size) into a CHECKED whole-file `[]char` view INSIDE the Eff. `zip` runs the map before
/// the size (left-to-right), so `arche_file_size` reads the size stashed by the map. The raw address is never
/// sliceable on its own — `mem.bound` is the single audited FFI pointer→slice door.
file_map :: func(own path: []char) -> Eff([]char) {
  return zip(arche_file_map(move path), arche_file_size())
    |> mem.bound;
}
